th fake tokenizer/accounting dependency and stub transport. Feed over-budget document; assert configured policy outcome (truncate or reject) and verify dispatch behavior matches policy (send adjusted request or no send).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.34,"Integration":0.58,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Provider-reported token usage for a typical document remains within configured per-call budget.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Test must use real provider responses and usage metadata; mocks can hide over-budget behavior caused by actual model outputs/formatting. Because execution path relies on real AI API behavior, Integration is too low. Rejected Workflow since this is one model call’s budget property, not multi-step agent chaining.","test_description":"Run live classification on representative documents, capture provider usage fields (input/output/total tokens), and assert total usage is <= configured budget for each call; fail on any over-budget live result.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.3,"Agentic":0.64,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"On provider rate-limit signal, module waits and retries instead of surfacing immediate error.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is retry orchestration across module boundaries (error classifier, backoff policy, retry loop, caller return). A stub provider can deterministically emit rate-limit then success to reproduce failure. Rejected System because real network is not necessary to validate wait/retry control flow. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because correctness is infrastructure logic, not model decision quality or multi-step agent pipeline.","test_description":"Wire module to a fake provider that returns rate-limit error then success. Use controllable clock/backoff hook to verify delay occurs and final result is returned without propagating transient error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.69,"System":0.24,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
